  "prompt": "What is the minimum rank required in KVPY for IISER?",
  "response": "The **Kishore Vaigyanik Protsahan Yojana (KVPY)** is a prestigious fellowship program in India that encourages students to pursue careers in research. While KVPY is not directly an entrance exam for **Indian Institutes of Science Education and Research (IISERs)**, it is highly relevant because IISERs consider KVPY ranks for admissions.\n\n### KVPY and IISER Admission:\n- IISERs offer admissions to their **5-year BS-MS dual degree program** through multiple channels, including:\n  1. **IISER Aptitude Test (IAT)**\n  2. **KVPY fellowship holders**\n  3. **JEE Advanced ranks (for some IISERs)**\n- Students who qualify for the **KVPY fellowship** (SA/SX/SB streams) are eligible for direct admission to IISERs without appearing for the IAT.\n\n### Minimum Rank for IISER Admission via KVPY:\nThere is **no fixed minimum rank** declared by IISERs for KVPY-qualified students. However, based on historical data and trends:\n- Candidates with a **KVPY rank within the top 500-600** (SA/SX/SB streams) have a high chance of securing admission to IISERs.\n- For the **SA stream** (Class 12 students), a rank within **300-400** is generally considered safe.\n- For the **SX stream** (Class 12 students with science streams), a rank within **200-300** is usually competitive.\n- For the **SB stream** (1st-year UG students), a rank within **100-150** is often sufficient.\n\n### Important Notes:\n- The cutoff ranks may vary slightly each year based on the number of KVPY applicants, IISER seats, and overall competition.\n- IISERs prioritize KVPY fellowship holders, but admission is also dependent on seat availability and counseling processes.\n\nIf you have qualified for KVPY, it is advisable to participate in the IISER counseling process, as securing a rank within the top few hundred significantly increases your chances of admission.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
